bounding_box:
bounding_box(shape: Shape) → {undefined}

Returns a lambda function that contains the coordinates of the bounding box. Provided with the axis 'x', 'y' or 'z' and value 'min' for minimum and 'max' for maximum, it returns the coordinates of the bounding box.

For example
clone:
clone(shape: Shape) → {Shape}

Creates a clone of the specified Shape.

render:
render() → {RenderGroup}

Renders using any Shapes stored thus far. The Shapes will then not be included in any subsequent renders.
render_axis:
render_axis() → {RenderGroup}

Renders using any Shapes stored thus far, along with an axis. The Shapes will then not be included in any subsequent renders.
render_grid:
render_grid() → {RenderGroup}

Renders using any Shapes stored thus far, along with a grid. The Shapes will then not be included in any subsequent renders.
render_grid_axis:
render_grid_axis() → {RenderGroup}

Renders using any Shapes stored thus far, along with a grid and axis. The Shapes will then not be included in any subsequent renders.
rotate:
rotate(shape: Shape, x: number, y: number, z: number) → {Shape}

Rotate the shape by the provided angles in the x, y and z direction. Angles provided are in the form of radians (i.e. 2π represent 360 degrees)
rotate_x:
rotate_x(shape: Shape, x: number) → {Shape}

Rotate the shape by the provided angles in the x direction. Angles provided are in the form of radians (i.e. 2π represent 360 degrees)
rotate_y:
rotate_y(shape: Shape, y: number) → {Shape}

Rotate the shape by the provided angles in the y direction. Angles provided are in the form of radians (i.e. 2π represent 360 degrees)
rotate_z:
rotate_z(shape: Shape, z: number) → {Shape}

Rotate the shape by the provided angles in the z direction. Angles provided are in the form of radians (i.e. 2π represent 360 degrees)
scale:
scale(shape: Shape, x: number, y: number, z: number) → {Shape}

Scales the shape in the x, y and z direction with the specified factor, ranging from 0 to infinity. For example scaling the shape by 1 in x, y and z direction results in the original shape.
scale_x:
scale_x(shape: Shape, x: number) → {Shape}

Scales the shape in the x direction with the specified factor, ranging from 0 to infinity. For example scaling the shape by 1 in x direction results in the original shape.
scale_y:
scale_y(shape: Shape, y: number) → {Shape}

Scales the shape in the y direction with the specified factor, ranging from 0 to infinity. For example scaling the shape by 1 in y direction results in the original shape.
scale_z:
scale_z(shape: Shape, z: number) → {Shape}

Scales the shape in the z direction with the specified factor, ranging from 0 to infinity. For example scaling the shape by 1 in z direction results in the original shape.
shape_center:
shape_center(shape: Shape) → {undefined}

Returns a lambda function that contains the center of the given shape in the x, y and z direction. Providing 'x', 'y', 'z' as input would return x, y and z coordinates of shape's center

For example
shape_set_center:
shape_set_center(shape: Shape, x: number, y: number, z: number) → {Shape}

Set the center of the shape with the provided x, y and z coordinates.
store:
store(shape: Shape) → {void}

Stores a clone of the specified Shape for later rendering. Its colour defaults to the module's provided silver colour variable.
store_as_color:
store_as_color(shape: Shape, hex: string) → {void}

Colours a clone of the specified Shape using the specified hex colour code, then stores it for later rendering. You may use one of the colour variables provided by the module, or you may specify your own custom colour code.

Colour codes must be of the form "#XXXXXX" or "XXXXXX", where each X represents a non-case sensitive hexadecimal number. Invalid colour codes default to black.
store_as_rgb:
store_as_rgb(shape: Shape, redComponent: number, greenComponent: number, blueComponent: number) → {void}

Colours a clone of the specified Shape using the specified RGB values, then stores it for later rendering.

RGB values are clamped between 0 and 1.
subtract:
subtract(a: Shape, b: Shape) → {Shape}

Subtraction of the second shape from the first shape to produce a new shape.
translate:
translate(shape: Shape, x: number, y: number, z: number) → {Shape}

Translate / Move the shape by the provided x, y and z units from negative infinity to infinity.
translate_x:
translate_x(shape: Shape, x: number) → {Shape}

Translate / Move the shape by the provided x units from negative infinity to infinity.
translate_y:
translate_y(shape: Shape, y: number) → {Shape}

Translate / Move the shape by the provided y units from negative infinity to infinity.
translate_z:
translate_z(shape: Shape, z: number) → {Shape}

Translate / Move the shape by the provided z units from negative infinity to infinity.
union:
union(a: Shape, b: Shape) → {Shape}

Union of the two provided shapes to produce a new shape.
volume:
volume(shape: Shape) → {number}

Measure the volume of the provided shape.
